FBIS4-32920 "drlat104_g_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-104 Daily Report 26 May 1994 Guatemala Government-URNG Peace Talks Conclude in Puebla Government-URNG Peace Talks Conclude in Puebla PA2805023094 Guatemala City Televisiete Television in Spanish 0400 GMT 26 May 94 PA2805023094 Guatemala City Televisiete Television Spanish BFN [From the "Channel 7 News" newscast] [Text] The Guatemalan Government and the National Guatemalan Revolutionary Unity have outlined the guidelines for a national effort to solve in the short term the problem those persons displaced by the war, UN mediator Jean Arnoult has reported. On Wednesday, the delegates concluded four days of debates in Puebla, Mexico, on the resettlement of the displaced. The sides have decided to resume the talks next week and reach a definitive agreement on the subject. The mediator has announced the postponement of the round of talks slated to be held from 31 May to 3 June in Oslo, Norway, where the creation of a commission to investigate human rights violations during the three-decades-long war will be discussed.
